OL,3,C'Calm before the storm': Inflation
OL,4,Cfalls to 2.6% ahead of April's rising
OL,5,Cbills
OL,7,F"That is why the Government has
OL,8,Fboosted pay for three million people
OL,9,Fby increasing the minimum wage, frozen
OL,10,Ffuel duty and begun rolling out free
OL,11,Fbreakfast clubs in primary schools."
OL,13,FThe decrease has been largely
OL,14,Fattributed to a fall in petrol prices.
OL,16,FRobert Wood, chief UK economist at
OL,17,FPantheon Macroeconomics, said: "Weekly
OL,18,Fmotor fuels price data point to a 1.1%
OL,19,Fmonth-to-month fall, well below the
OL,20,F1.9% gain a year ago.
